text: Bon Accord is a locality in the North Burnett Region, Queensland, Australia. In the , Bon Accord had a population of 19 people. == History == Bon Accord Provisional School opened about September 1901. It became Bon Accord State School on 1 January 1909. Due to low attendances, it closed about May 1922. == References == c Category:North Burnett Region Category:Localities in Queensland
